{
  "esm": "0.4.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "UrbanCanopyModel",
    "description": "Top-level composed diagnostic urban canopy model following the Community Land Model Urban (CLMU) parameterization of Oleson et al. (2010). Wires four CLMU subsystems \u2014 OfflineModeForcing (raw met \u2192 derived forcing), CLMUAtmosphere (atmospheric interface diagnostics), UrbanRadiation (solar/longwave radiation), and HeatMomentumFluxes (Monin-Obukhov surface fluxes) \u2014 via top-level coupling equations. All subsystems are inlined (ESS spec \u00a74.7 composed-model pattern). Surface temperatures are prescribed as parameters (diagnostic mode). Migrated from UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4 src/urban_canopy_model.jl:41.",
    "tags": [
      "urban_canopy",
      "clmu",
      "composed",
      "diagnostic"
    ],
    "created": "2026-05-21T00:00:00Z",
    "authors": [
      "UrbanCanopy.jl contributors",
      "EarthSciModels migration (esm-vmik)"
    ],
    "references": [
      {
        "citation": "Oleson, K. W., G. B. Bonan, J. J. Feddema, M. Vertenstein, and E. Kluzek (2010). Technical Description of an Urban Parameterization for the Community Land Model (CLMU). NCAR Technical Note NCAR/TN-480+STR. Chapters 1-3, 6."
      }
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "UrbanCanopyModel": {
      "reference": {
        "notes": "source_ref: UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4f15609f20339d3a7d104de8064544310:src/urban_canopy_model.jl:41\n\nComposed model (ESS spec \u00a74.7) following the SulfateFormation / WaterVaporThermodynamics pattern: four subsystems inlined under 'subsystems', top-level coupling equations wire the data flow.\n\nSubsystem inlining avoids SubsystemRef dependencies on .esm files that may not yet be on main (the original rejection on esm-vmik was SubsystemRefError for heat_momentum_fluxes.esm). All subsystem content is self-contained here.\n\nHeatMomentumFluxes (flux subsystem): the \u03c8_m/\u03c8_h piecewise stability functions produce deeply nested ifelse expressions. Under cse=False the _flat_to_sympy_rhs substitution chain explodes (~419K ops). This file is listed in CSE_TRUE_OVERRIDE_FILENAMES in tools/run_esm_inline_tests.py; ULP-equivalence of cse=True \u2194 cse=False was verified by esm-wqy1.\n\nVariable naming: offline/atmos subsystems use ASCII (theta_atm, rho_atm, z_prime_atm following their standalone ESM convention); rad uses Unicode (\u03bc_zen, \u03b1_*, \u03b5_* following urban_radiation.esm); flux uses ASCII (theta_atm, rho_atm, zeta_in following the ASCII convention of sibling subsystems). Coupling equations bridge the name differences.\n\nTolerance: model-level rel=1e-6 (composed algebraic system, no ODE integration; the piecewise \u03c8 stability functions involve logarithms and cube-roots, ULP roundoff ~1e-15 at non-degenerate stability; rel=1e-6 gives comfortable headroom above ULP and matches the composed precedents SulfateFormation and WaterVaporThermodynamics)."
      },
      "tolerance": {
        "rel": 1e-06
      },
      "variables": {
        "S_atm": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "W/m^2",
          "default": 500.0,
          "description": "Total incident solar radiation (Eq. 6.1 output)"
        },
        "T_atm": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "K",
          "default": 293.15,
          "description": "Atmospheric temperature"
        },
        "P_atm": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "Pa",
          "default": 101325.0,
          "description": "Atmospheric pressure"
        },
        "q_atm": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "kg/kg",
          "default": 0.01,
          "description": "Atmospheric specific humidity"
        },
        "W_atm": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "m/s",
          "default": 7.071,
          "description": "Atmospheric wind speed"
        },
        "P_precip": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Total precipitation rate"
        },
        "\u03bc_zen": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "rad",
          "default": 0.5236,
          "description": "Solar zenith angle (30\u00b0)"
        },
        "H_W": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 1.0,
          "description": "Canyon H/W ratio"
        },
        "W_roof": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 0.5,
          "description": "Roof fraction"
        },
        "H_canyon": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "m",
          "default": 10.0,
          "description": "Canyon height"
        },
        "f_prvrd": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 0.5,
          "description": "Pervious road fraction"
        },
        "H_w_est": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "m",
          "default": 5.0,
          "description": "Height for canyon wind estimate"
        },
        "z_0": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "m",
          "default": 1.0,
          "description": "Roughness length"
        },
        "z_d": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "m",
          "default": 5.0,
